 countries, the pace of the transition, the management of multi-level governance systems, the pros and cons of different policy instruments, the planning of low-carbon infrastructures, the roles and meanings of energy justice. The Handbook can be drawn upon by legal scholars to compare decarbonisation pathways in several jurisdictions. Non-legal scholars can find information to be included in transition theories and decarbonization scenarios. Policymakers can discover contextual factors that should be taken into account when deciding how to support the transition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aEnergy law. 7aLAW / Public.2bisacsh  aenergy law, climate law, environmental law, low-carbon transition.1 aAddaney, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnglés Hernández, Marisol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArrobbio, Osman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasu, Arindam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellantuono, Giuseppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellantuono, Giuseppe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBellera Landa, Isabella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenjamin, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhullar, Lovleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaten, Thijs ten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCerny, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChege, Kennedy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChikanayev, Shaimerden, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go